description: Test the relay to determine whether it is switching on and off periodically, and if it is causing the lamp to turn off every 20 seconds., outcome='The Control Relay is currently closed (switched on) and does not show any observable internal faults. The Main Load (lamp) is not lit and also shows no observable internal faults.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=25.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Switched output cables (from ambient sensor module),
description: Measure voltage across the switched output cables from the ambient sensor module to check whether 12V is present during the lamp-off period., outcome="Voltage measured at 'Control Output Cable (+)' is 0.3592 V, and at 'Control Output Cable (−)' is 0.0003 V, both relative to ground. There is no evidence of 12V present during the lamp-off period. No polarity inversion detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Relay coil drive/input (ambient sensor module),
description: Measure the control voltage at the relay coil or the drive signal from the sensor circuit to verify if the control signal is responsible for the periodic opening of the relay, despite it currently testing closed., outcome='The control relay coil shows a voltage of 11.9873 V at its positive terminal and 0.3592 V at its negative terminal. The ambient light sensor shows 0.119 V at its positive terminal and 0.0003 V at its negative terminal. No polarity inversions are detected in these measurements.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> switched cables relay contacts (ambient sensor module),
description: Test continuity across the relay switched contacts while the coil is energized (relay should be 'closed'). Verify if there is reliable conduction through the relay when it is supposed to be closed, or if there is high resistance/open contact due to faulty relay contacts., outcome="The measured resistance across the 'Control Relay' switched contacts is 0.01 Ω, which matches the nominal value. Reliable conduction is present, and there is no indication of a faulty relay contact. No polarity inversion is indicated.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=20.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> lamp indicator (small bulb in load module),
description: Measure the voltage across the lamp indicator terminals during both the on and off periods of the main lamp to determine if the indicator receives voltage when the main lamp is off., outcome='Both the internal indicator lamp and the main lamp show approximately 0.0003 V across their terminals, indicating that neither is receiving significant voltage. No polarity inversion is detected from the voltage measurement results provided.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=45.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> switched output cables (ambient sensor module),
description: Measure voltage across the switched output cables during the main lamp's ON period (when the lamp is actually illuminated) to see if 12V is present, and compare with OFF period measurements already obtained., outcome='During the main lamp ON period, the voltage at Control Output Cable (+) is 0.36\u202fV and at Control Output Cable (−) is 0.0003\u202fV. No significant voltage (e.g., 12\u202fV) is present across these output cables.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Switched cables indicator LED (ambient sensor module),
description: Measure voltage across the switched cables indicator LED inside the ambient sensor module to determine if it is receiving power, and visually inspect if it illuminates during the periods when the main lamp is expected to be ON., outcome='Diagnostic summary: The PSU Status LED (green) measures 1.2916 V at the anode relative to ground and 0.0 V at the cathode, and it is visually confirmed to be illuminated with no observable internal faults. This indicates the LED is receiving power and operating as expected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=30.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> unswitched input cables (ambient sensor module),
description: Measure the voltage at the unswitched input cables (i.e., the input to the relay circuit from the PSU) to confirm whether 12V is present before the relay. This establishes whether power is reaching the control module from the PSU., outcome='Voltage at the PSU Output Cable (+) and Control Input Cable (+) is approximately 12V with respect to ground, while both (−) cables are near 0V. No polarity inversion detected; cable polarities are consistent at the relay input. Power is present at the input to the control module.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=80.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
